<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: PVP Will NEVER be balanced.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Phazer">Phazer</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:27 p.m. 3/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: PVP Will NEVER be balanced.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1995" TARGET=_self>PVP Will NEVER be balanced.</A> (The RealmWeaver)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Don't fool yourselves into thinking PVP in EverQuest will ever

<BR>&gt; be refined and balanced, because changing the classes to balance
<BR>&gt; PVP would mean shfting the balance of NON-PVP. And Verant will
<BR>&gt; never risk upsetting the 90% of the players who play non-PVP to
<BR>&gt; "appease" the PVP players. PVP in EQ will always be
<BR>&gt; imbalanced. Accept it now and don't expect any change or you
<BR>&gt; will be sorely disappointed.
<P>Actually, I believe it is refined and balanced to some point. Perhaps the melee classes might have a small disadvantage, it's still all out of fun. Who cares about the 90% of the other players, they are totally missing out on a new concept of gameplay. I'm having fun every minute, and it only goes up hill from here.
<P>Just wait 'till the big wars come. Fun.
<P>Phazling
<BR>Phazling / Rallos Zek
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
